The paper introduces a new type of LSTM cell that reduces the number of parameters and FLOPS required for evaluation, making it potentially faster and smaller than regular LSTMs. The experimental evaluation focuses on handwriting recognition datasets, which are commonly studied in the computer vision and natural language processing fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
